<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1845-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1845-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="36" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 29.</note>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Pakenham</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Buchanan</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1845-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 29, 1845.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>* * * The undersigned, therefore, trusts that the American
                            plenipotentiary will be prepared to offer some further proposal for the
                            settlement of the Oregon question more consistent with fairness and
                            equity, and with the reasonable expectations of the British government,
                            as defined in the statement marked D, which the undersigned had the
                            honor to present to the American plenipotentiary at the early part of
                            the present negotiation.<seg type="margin">Mr. Pakenham rejects Mr.
                                Buchanan’s offer.</seg></p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>R. PAKENHAM.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">James Buchanan</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>